1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 10=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:35,110 --> 00:00:36,670
The nether tomb?

4
00:00:38,110 --> 00:00:39,000
What spirit?

5
00:00:39,470 --> 00:00:40,390
What ghost?

6
00:00:40,736 --> 00:00:41,949
In China, it's called a ghost.

7
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:43,316
In the West, it's called a spirit.

8
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:45,280
Isn't it the same thing?

9
00:00:48,030 --> 00:00:49,430
Maybe I'm using the wrong word.

10
00:00:49,499 --> 00:00:51,219
But I really don't know
how to describe it.

11
00:00:51,670 --> 00:00:53,470
Calling it a ghost isn't quite right.

12
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,200
I've heard many people talk about it.

13
00:00:55,670 --> 00:00:57,470
It's not some feudal superstition.

14
00:00:57,670 --> 00:00:59,710
It's a special physical phenomenon.

15
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:02,470
There's no specific term for it yet.

16
00:01:02,790 --> 00:01:05,230
Maybe calling it a spirit
is more appropriate.

17
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:08,230
Even so, it has to come from somewhere.

18
00:01:08,990 --> 00:01:09,840
This...

19
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:11,790
Whose spirit is this?

20
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:16,040
I think it's the spirit
of a Western Zhou tomb.

21
00:01:16,430 --> 00:01:17,560
It's not the kind of spirit

22
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:19,590
that forms after someone dies.

23
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,433
Instead, the Western Zhou tomb itself

24
00:01:21,444 --> 00:01:22,430
is the spirit.

25
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,230
In our geomancy profession,

26
00:01:24,230 --> 00:01:25,870
it's the legendary nether tomb.

27
00:01:26,230 --> 00:01:27,400
A Western Zhou nether tomb

28
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:30,350
attached to this Tang mausoleum.

29
00:01:30,710 --> 00:01:31,950
Superstition.

30
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:35,760
This isn't superstition.

31
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:37,060
It's just a way of describing it.

32
00:01:37,350 --> 00:01:38,560
All signs indicate

33
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:40,106
that both the Tang and the Western Zhou

34
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:42,400
favored Yunling
as a Feng Shui treasure land.

35
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,400
Most likely in the Western Zhou period,

36
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,780
someone had already chosen it.

37
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:46,950
But at that time,

38
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:48,120
Feng Shui theory wasn't

39
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,506
as developed as it was in the Tang.

40
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:51,760
Yet the unity of heaven and man

41
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:53,760
has always been
humanity's ultimate pursuit.

42
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:55,200
By the Tang dynasty,

43
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:57,820
a Feng Shui master who surveyed land
for the imperial family

44
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,280
also chose Yunling as a treasure site,

45
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:02,400
so they used the structure
of the Western Zhou tomb

46
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,230
to build the mausoleum.

47
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:06,790
You mean

48
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,310
the Western Zhou tomb

49
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:10,870
and the Tang tomb
became mixed together?

50
00:02:11,430 --> 00:02:12,400
You could say that.

51
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:14,590
So, that means

52
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:16,120
as long as we determine

53
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:17,710
which dynasty this tomb belongs to,

54
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:19,310
we can get out.

55
00:02:20,019 --> 00:02:20,992
That should be the case.

56
00:02:22,190 --> 00:02:25,310
The Shang and Zhou tombs weren't
as luxurious as the Tang ones.

57
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,840
This place certainly isn't luxurious.

58
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:30,120
Look at it.

59
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,820
It's so poor there's nothing but stairs.

60
00:02:31,986 --> 00:02:34,782
The Shang and Zhou tombs were built
with huge stones and grand halls,

61
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,150
and they had many floors.

62
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:37,370
They weren't flat structures.

63
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,190
Their scale was much larger
than that of the Tang tombs.

64
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:42,470
Very large indeed.

65
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:43,960
Good grief.

66
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,680
My legs are about to break.

67
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:48,960
So, we can basically confirm

68
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:51,430
this space should belong
to the Western Zhou.

69
00:02:52,590 --> 00:02:54,310
If this is a Western Zhou tomb,

70
00:02:54,426 --> 00:02:56,030
the two staircases beside the stone wall

71
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:57,910
should lead to the very top of the tomb.

72
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,030
We already walked one of them.

73
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:02,590
So, this one should lead us out.

74
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,590
Let's go.

75
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:08,400
Come on, Lu.

76
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:26,810
Darn it.

77
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,280
Aren't we back here again?

78
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,506
Huang Long, what are you doing?

79
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:32,310
Didn't you say we could get out?

80
00:03:33,030 --> 00:03:34,150
As Marx said,

81
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:36,800
practice is the sole criterion
for testing truth.

82
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,680
This practice only proves

83
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,430
this isn't a Western Zhou tomb.

84
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:44,150
You're using Marx to mess with me?

85
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,800
My wrong judgment misled everyone.

86
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:49,560
That's my responsibility.

87
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,470
How affectionate.

88
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:53,823
Believe it or not, I'll send you both

89
00:03:53,834 --> 00:03:55,280
to meet your maker together.

90
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:57,280
Huang Long, put the gun down.

91
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:58,560
The boss sent you here

92
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,800
not to sabotage things.

93
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,400
Your boss told you to put the gun down.

94
00:04:15,910 --> 00:04:18,070
Only this downward staircase
hasn't been tried yet.

95
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,680
Downward.

96
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,440
Chubby,

97
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,680
I can't walk anymore.

98
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:35,630
My blood sugar is low.

99
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,510
Bro, it's still the same place.

100
00:04:40,430 --> 00:04:42,950
I still have an 80-year-old mother.

101
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:44,630
Now, I won't see her again.

102
00:04:45,830 --> 00:04:46,750
Stop talking nonsense.

103
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:47,903
Dying here would be pathetic.

104
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,800
Now, it's time to test the theory.

105
00:04:52,070 --> 00:04:53,480
Wait, Chen.

106
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:54,680
What do you mean?

107
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:57,870
I noticed a crescent mark
every 23 steps.

108
00:04:57,950 --> 00:04:59,040
That forms a cycle.

109
00:04:59,456 --> 00:05:01,139
In the 16-character
Feng Shui secret arts,

110
00:05:01,150 --> 00:05:02,310
there's a word called Dun.

111
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,000
(Dun)
It talks

112
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,040
about traps in ancient tombs.

113
00:05:06,510 --> 00:05:08,120
China has always valued numerology.

114
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:11,160
So, tomb structures always follow it.

115
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:14,910
And then?

116
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:16,310
I studied it carefully.

117
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:17,560
Thinking back now,

118
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:20,240
this kind of 23-step staircase

119
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:23,310
is technically called
a soul-locking stair.

120
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,920
It's not always exactly 23 steps.

121
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,240
But with this number,

122
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,040
we can calculate
how many steps lead us out.

123
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,430
Are you sure this time?

124
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:34,630
In theory, yes.

125
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:35,920
So, we have to test it.

126
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:37,560
Chubby, give me a piece of candy.

127
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,360
No need to trouble you.

128
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,310
I'll be back soon.

129
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,190
Chen, I'll go with you.

130
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:48,240
We'll go.

131
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,080
Stop.

132
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:52,790
Chen Youxi,

133
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,120
you go alone.

134
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,200
Go ahead.

135
00:06:49,430 --> 00:06:50,270
The rope.

136
00:06:51,190 --> 00:06:52,600
- Rope.
- Here.

137
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:50,136
The rope is almost gone again.

138
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,000
Is Chen okay?

139
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,320
Yes.

140
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:55,510
If something happened,
the rope wouldn't move.

141
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:01,099
Why did the rope stop moving?

142
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,520
It reached the end.

143
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:14,670
Who?

144
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:18,920
Chen.

145
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,600
Why did you come back from that side?

146
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,160
I left marks along the path

147
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,310
we just walked.

148
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:26,360
Now, I can return from anywhere I want.

149
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,120
Then what ghost was trapping us here?

150
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,819
This is the soul-locking stair.

151
00:08:31,830 --> 00:08:34,360
When you're inside it,
you only see one staircase.

152
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:36,200
But in reality, it leads everywhere.

153
00:08:40,670 --> 00:08:42,150
This cycle,

154
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:43,440
formed by 23 steps,

155
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:45,550
is actually a numerical hypnosis method.

156
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,270
The crescent marks are the traps.

157
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:52,720
These marks gradually shift
along the steps.

158
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,600
And the steps and stone walls

159
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:57,550
may be coated with an ancient formula

160
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,720
that absorbs light,

161
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:01,720
making it even harder to tell direction.

162
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,550
Once you start noticing signs
like the marks,

163
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:06,910
your logical judgment gets confused.

164
00:09:08,196 --> 00:09:09,550
You think you're walking straight,

165
00:09:09,550 --> 00:09:12,150
but unknowingly, you turn onto a fork.

166
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:14,000
Then you keep circling on that fork

167
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:17,360
until you completely lose
your sense of direction.

168
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,580
The steps have
small height differences and are wide.

169
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:40,080
The length of the steps

170
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:42,080
spreads out that tiny height difference.

171
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:44,390
It creates the illusion
of elevation change,

172
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,550
making people think
they're going up or down stairs.

173
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:50,200
Do I look blind to you?

174
00:09:50,510 --> 00:09:52,440
These stairs have no elevation change?

175
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,630
They do,

176
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,360
but the builder
of the soul-locking stair

177
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,840
used these changes

178
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,080
to give psychological hints.

179
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,000
Whether you go up or down the stairs,

180
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:04,120
you're actually just circling
on a flat plane.

181
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,870
No wonder we kept wandering so long.

182
00:10:10,530 --> 00:10:11,390
Chen,

183
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:13,200
practice does lead to knowledge.

184
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:16,080
So, where exactly is the exit?

185
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:18,910
Follow me if you want.

186
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,030
If you don't understand,

187
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,320
feel free to consult.

188
00:10:21,510 --> 00:10:23,720
Telegram number: 0323.

189
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,750
The exit should be ahead.

190
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:53,870
Slow down.

191
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,266
Don't trigger your illness again.

192
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,550
Why does it suddenly feel so hot?

193
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,200
Yeah, look.

194
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:54,320
What is that stuff flowing down there?

195
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,280
Is it magma?

196
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:05,240
That gate

197
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:06,840
is built quite grandly.

198
00:12:08,390 --> 00:12:10,790
This should be the entrance
to the main hall.

199
00:12:11,390 --> 00:12:12,230
Possibly.

200
00:13:04,270 --> 00:13:05,360
What is that thing?

201
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:07,143
Why are there so many spikes on it?

202
00:13:08,790 --> 00:13:09,840
Blade cart!

203
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:11,670
What's a blade cart?

204
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,270
On ancient battlefields,

205
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:15,390
defenders used it to fight desperately.

206
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:16,510
This is bad.

207
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:18,150
When the stone gate fully opens,

208
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,790
that blade cart will roll down.

209
00:13:19,790 --> 00:13:20,416
Chubby.

210
00:13:20,463 --> 00:13:21,840
Find a way to pull the gate closed.

211
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,350
- Okay.
- Be careful.

212
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:29,200
It won't come down.

213
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,480
See if there's a mechanism.

214
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,320
I... This...

215
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,000
Chen, what do we do?

216
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:39,110
What else can we do?

217
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,120
We fall back first.

218
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:40,960
You cover the rear.

219
00:13:41,030 --> 00:13:41,910
How loyal.

220
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:43,510
- Run!
- Hurry!

221
00:14:00,430 --> 00:14:03,530
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

222
00:14:05,210 --> 00:14:08,890
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

223
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:14,530
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

224
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:21,680
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

225
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:33,260
♪La la♪

226
00:14:40,010 --> 00:14:42,000
♪No line divides the border♪

227
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,780
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

228
00:14:44,780 --> 00:14:47,150
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

229
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:49,840
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

230
00:14:51,340 --> 00:14:53,050
♪Hey hey hey♪

231
00:14:54,380 --> 00:14:56,200
♪Hey hey hey♪

232
00:14:58,850 --> 00:14:59,850
♪Hey hey♪

233
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,000
♪Hey hey♪

234
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:03,540
♪Hey hey♪

235
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:09,370
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

236
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:13,670
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

237
00:15:15,950 --> 00:15:18,170
♪No difference between you and me♪

238
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:20,780
♪No lead or side role on this stage♪

239
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:22,990
♪A perfect life is something we share♪

240
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:25,490
♪Love declares across the sky and earth♪

241
00:15:26,420 --> 00:15:31,210
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

242
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:36,060
♪Time and space go beyond all bounds♪

243
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:40,910
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

244
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:43,000
♪This is our world♪

245
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:48,030
♪Shining lives bring the change♪

246
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:55,120
♪In a blink, to forever♪
